@979  = ~You have indeed free me, my good <PRO_SIRMAAM>!~
@980  = ~Yes, I did. Am I hero enough for you now?~
@981  = ~My Fair Lady, your favor filled me with strength and valor. The victory is as much yours as it is mine.~
@982  = ~I... I think so. Oh, Sime must you invent some ridiculous trials? Do not you know that I love you?~
@983  = ~I never doubted that you are a hero. But now I can tell everyone, that the <PRO_MANWOMAN> I love saved me from the clutches of an evil dragon. It was worth a trip!~
@984  = ~Such gallantry! I only pity that I did not join you in the fight! Next time...~
@985  = ~No next time, my Fair Lady. The deal was one salvation for one wedding. I cannot marry you more than once, can I?~
@986  = ~Next time we will head a host of riders to fight some evil lord... or fight in a tourney... we cannot do dragons all the time. It will be ultimately boring, my Lady.~
@987  = ~Yes, dear. (Keldorn said it usually works...)~
@988  = ~Oh... I see. Well, we can do something different then. How about a tourney?~
@989  = ~You have a point. Let it be an evil lord next. But our time is up now...~
@990  = ~Hmm, sounds good. But what was that thing about Keldorn you muttered? Never mind, we must go now.~
